
Hardening your Linux box with a firewall isn't that easy even for experts.
FREEDWALL is just this: an iptables rules generator meant to be easy to configure and deploy.


#############################################################################
# Features: 								    #
#############################################################################

    * systemD compliant start/stop method
    * System V compliant start/stop method
    * 3 configuration zones: LOCALHOST, LOCALNET, WORLD
    * protection against Xmas, Null & FIN Scan
    * block remote uptime discovery
    * masquerading autodetection
    * system hardening through sysctl directives
    * TCP/UDP port forwarding
    * ICMP filtering
    * IPV6 filtering
    * host/port based Blacklists & Whitelists
    * load/unload iptables modules
    * GRSEC patch support
    * White/Black lists
    * native support for Spotify, Chromecast, mDNS and multicast protocols


#############################################################################


